---
title: Teriyaki Chicken Stir-Fry with Jasmine Rice and Sugar Snap Peas
description: Soy to the world! The time for a simple stir-fry recipe has come. This chicken is tossed in a thick teriyaki glaze, which coats each piece in a flavorful blend of soy sauce, garlic, ginger, and sesame. Served atop a bed of jasmine rice with sugar snap peas to the side, the result is a tour de force of Asian-style flavors that both kids and adults will find easy to love.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/teriyaki-chicken-tenders-f2ea8fe8.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/teriyaki-chicken-tenders-5b16cb16ae08b533b21a1862-0b5284ee.pdf
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 720 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 4.5 g
  carbohydrates: 88 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 900 mg
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/teriyaki-chicken-tenders-5b16cb16ae08b533b21a1862
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring 1¼ cups water and
a @salt{pinch} to a boil in a #medium pot{}. Peel @ginger{1%thumb} and mince
until you have 1 TBSP. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim, then thinly slice
@scallions{2}, keeping greens and whites separate. Halve @lime{1}; cut one half
into wedges.

Once water is boiling, add @jasmine rice{3/4%cup} to pot. Cover, lower heat,
and reduce to a simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Remove from heat
and keep covered.

Trim any tough ends or strings from @sugar snap peas{6%ounce}, then toss with a
large drizzle of oil on a #baking sheet{}. Season with @salt and @pepper.
Roast in oven until crisp at edges, ~{10-12%minutes}. Once done, toss snap peas
with @sesame oil{1%tsp}, @sesame seeds{1%tsp}, and a squeeze of lime (we sent
more oil and seeds).

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}. Add to pan
in a single layer and cook until browned but not cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes},
tossing once. Remove from pan and set aside.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Whisk
@soy sauce{3%tbsp}, @sugar{2%tbsp}, @white wine vinegar{1%tbsp}, and
@cornstarch{1/2%tsp} in a #small bowl{}. Put scallion whites, garlic, and
ginger in pan and cook, tossing, until softened, about ~{1%minute}. Stir in soy
sauce mixture and bring to a simmer. Let thicken slightly, about ~{1%minute}.

Return chicken to pan and toss to coat. Cook until no longer pink in center,
~{1-2%minutes}. Add a squeeze of lime to rice and fluff with a #fork{}. Divide
rice, snap peas, and chicken between plates. Drizzle with any remaining sauce.
Garnish to taste with scallion greens and remaining @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}
(you may not use all). Serve with lime wedges.

> This chicken stir-fry is a tour de force of Asian-style flavors that both kids
> and adults will find easy to love.